tafsir[2]{c,v,t}:
  39,70,"(And each soul) whether it is righteous or sinful (is paid in full for what it did) of good or evil. (And He is best aware of what they do) of good or evil."
  39,72,"(It is said (unto them)) the angels of the Fire say to them: (Enter ye the gates of hell to dwell therein) forever. (Thus hapless is the journey's end of the scorners) it is the abode of those who felt too proud to accept faith in the Scripture and Messenger."